          "correct": "a",
          "difficulty": "medium",
          "explanation": "0.1³ = 0.001. So ∛0.001 = 0.1."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch07_A_016",
          "text": "The cube of 15 is:",
          "options": { "a": "1225", "b": "3375", "c": "3125", "d": "1125" },
          "correct": "b",
          "difficulty": "easy",
          "explanation": "15³ = 15 × 15 × 15 = 225 × 15 = 3375."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch07_A_017",
          "text": "For finding ∛a using prime factorisation, prime factors must be grouped in sets of:",
