          "correct": "b",
          "difficulty": "easy",
          "explanation": "To find a cube root, prime factors must form complete groups of three."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch07_A_018",
          "text": "Which of the following equals ∛(125 × 64)?",
          "options": { "a": "√5000", "b": "∛125 × ∛64", "c": "20", "d": "Both b and c" },
          "correct": "d",
          "difficulty": "medium",
          "explanation": "∛(125 × 64) = ∛125 × ∛64 = 5 × 4 = 20. So both b and c are correct."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch07_A_019",
          "text": "The cube of −3 is:",
          "options": { "a": "9", "b": "−9", "c": "27", "d": "−27" },
          "correct": "d",
          "difficulty": "easy",
          "explanation": "(−3)³ = −3 × −3 × −3 = 9 × −3 = −27."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch07_A_020",
          "text": "The pattern for sum of consecutive odd numbers forming cubes: 3³ = ?",
          "options": { "a": "1 + 3 + 5", "b": "3 + 5 + 7", "c": "7 + 9 + 11", "d": "5 + 9 + 13" },
          "correct": "c",
          "difficulty": "medium",
          "explanation": "n³ = sum of n consecutive odd numbers starting at n² − n + 1. For n = 3: starting at 9 − 3 + 1 = 7. So 3³ = 7 + 9 + 11 = 27 ✓."
        }
      ]
